        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p><img loading="lazy" src="https://cdn.substack.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F902fa1ea-6e2e-44aa-82b3-1bf4d2d7ef37_1920x1080.jpeg" alt="Assimilation" class="img_ev3q"></p><p>Biological organisms programmed by the data structures that we call DNA have shaped the world for nearly 3.5 billion years.</p><p>Throughout this time period, all living things have battled resource scarcity in the physical environment to replicate their DNA from one generation to the next in the process of natural selection.</p><p>Read the article on:<br>
